  <li>one sense described in terms of another (<em>Synaesthesia.</em>)
    <ul>
      <li>Some sense combinations work better than others. Sight can often be described in terms of sound: ex. â€˜muted colorsâ€™, â€˜loud colorsâ€™</li>
      <li>Touch can be applied to sound. (ex. â€˜gravelly voiceâ€™ )</li>
      <li>Touch can also be applied to sight. (ex. â€˜warm colorsâ€™, â€˜cool tonesâ€™ )</li>
      <li>Smells described in terms of other senses do not produce a good effect.</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ul>

