<p>The grammatically incorrect use of words for creative expression (<em>Catechresis</em>). Catachresis is often used to convey extreme emotion or alienation. It is prominent in baroque literature and, more recently, in dadaist and surrealist literature. a sentence that is so wrong, it works!</p>

