<p>Contradictions, opposition, inversion and violation of expectation is at the heart of wit</p>

<p>Memorable Expressions follow two principles:</p>
<ul>
  <li>the moulding of something abstract into concrete metaphors,</li>
  <li>combination of two conflicting notions. e.g. Diverse Panel of Jews, Castle in the Air, Deafening Silence. The sounds of silence.</li>
  <li>Or both: Party Game for Horrible People</li>
</ul>

<p>Key to wit and humour: Make things interesting (OX1 instead of Oxford), Use metaphors (), use rarer words , exaggerate simple things   and understate big things, borrow from popular sources (Ars Longa, vita bravos)</p>

<ul>
  <li>Overstating the ordinary.</li>
</ul>

